<TITLE> RAB raids JMB den in capital </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 15 (bdnews24.com)Rapid Action Battalion has cracked down on a hideout of JMB militants on Thursday midnight in the capital's north Pirerbagh, Shewrapara in Mirpur, a highly-placed RAB official said. A RAB team in the evening arrested Mizan, an alleged JMB member, and later took him to track his other cohorts at 61/3 Pirerbagh, added the official who declined to be named. Mizan told RAB officers that his wife lived on the second floor of the building with their two children. When RAB member reached the apartment's door along with Mizan, he talked with his wife in a sign language. Right after that, his wife blasted a bomb from inside the apartment. The blast made a hole in the door but none was injured. bdn
